Use the standard library
This is how to parse_nested_parens of paren_string:
  Remember that depths is []
  Remember that current_depth is 0
  Remember that max_depth is 0
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this paren_string's length times:
    Remember that ch is item i in paren_string
    When ch is "(", then:
      Increase current_depth by 1
      When current_depth is more than max_depth, then:
        Remember that max_depth is current_depth
      End when
    End when
    When ch is ")", then:
      Decrease current_depth by 1
    End when
    When ch is " ", then:
      Add depths to max_depth
      Remember that max_depth is 0
      Remember that current_depth is 0
    End when
    Increase i by 1
  End do
  Add depths to max_depth
  The answer is depths
